---
interface Intergroup {
  name: string;
  url?: string;
  phone?: string;
}

interface Props {
  city: string;
  stateFull: string;
  areaDescription: string;
  neighborhoods: string;
  transitInfo?: string;
  population?: number;
  intergroup?: Intergroup;
  meetingCount?: number;
}

const { city, stateFull, areaDescription, neighborhoods, transitInfo, population, intergroup, meetingCount } = Astro.props;
---

<section class="section-card seo-content" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
  <h2 id="about-heading" class="section-title">About AA Meetings near {city}, {stateFull}</h2>
  <div class="seo-text">
    <p>Alcoholics Anonymous (AA) meetings in {city}, {stateFull} provide a supportive community for individuals seeking recovery from alcohol addiction. Whether you're new to recovery or have been sober for years, {city}'s AA community welcomes you with open arms.</p>

    {meetingCount && meetingCount > 0 && (
      <p>There are currently <strong>{meetingCount} AA meetings</strong> listed in and around {city}, making it one of the most active recovery communities in {stateFull}. According to <a href="https://www.aa.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">AA's General Service Office</a>, there are over 67,000 weekly AA meetings across the United States, and {city} contributes meaningfully to that network.</p>
    )}

    {population && (
      <p>{city} is home to approximately <strong>{population.toLocaleString()} residents</strong>, with AA meetings distributed across the {areaDescription} to ensure accessible support throughout the community.{meetingCount && population ? ` That's approximately ${Math.round((meetingCount / population) * 100000)} meetings per 100,000 residents, reflecting ${city}'s commitment to accessible recovery support.` : ''}</p>
    )}

    {intergroup && (
      <p>Local meetings in {city} are coordinated through the <strong>{intergroup.name}</strong>.{intergroup.url ? <> Visit <a href={intergroup.url} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">{intergroup.name}</a> for the most up-to-date meeting information and local contacts.</> : <> They serve as the primary point of contact for AA in the area.</>}</p>
    )}

    <h3>Types of AA Meetings Available in {city}</h3>
    <p><strong>Open Meetings:</strong> Anyone interested in learning about AA can attend, including family members, friends, and those curious about the program.</p>
    <p><strong>Closed Meetings:</strong> Reserved for individuals who have a desire to stop drinking. These meetings offer a more intimate setting for sharing.</p>
    <p><strong>Speaker Meetings:</strong> One or more members share their experience, strength, and hope with the group.</p>
    <p><strong>Discussion Meetings:</strong> Members discuss a topic related to recovery, with everyone having an opportunity to share.</p>
    <p><strong>Big Book/Step Study:</strong> Focused study of AA literature including the Big Book and the 12 Steps.</p>
    <p><strong>Beginner Meetings:</strong> Specifically designed for newcomers who may be attending their first meetings. These groups provide extra guidance on how AA works, the 12 Steps, and getting a sponsor.</p>
    <p><strong>Online/Virtual Meetings:</strong> Participate from anywhere via video or phone. Online AA meetings have grown significantly since 2020 and now represent approximately 30% of all meetings nationwide, providing critical access for those who cannot attend in person.</p>

    <h3>Finding the Right Meeting in {city}</h3>
    <p>Use the filters above to find meetings that fit your schedule and preferences. Meetings are available throughout {areaDescription} including neighborhoods such as {neighborhoods}.</p>

    {transitInfo && (
      <>
        <h3>Getting to AA Meetings in {city}</h3>
        <p>{transitInfo} The MyMeetings app shows the exact address for every meeting location so you can plan your route in advance—no matter how you're getting there.</p>
      </>
    )}

    <h3>Recovery Resources in {city}</h3>
    <p>In addition to AA meetings, {city} residents can access recovery support through the <a href="https://www.samhsa.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration (SAMHSA)</a>, which provides a national helpline (1-800-662-4357) and treatment locator. The <a href="https://www.niaaa.nih.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">National Institute on Alcohol Abuse and Alcoholism (NIAAA)</a> offers evidence-based research confirming that consistent participation in peer support groups like AA significantly improves long-term sobriety outcomes.</p>

    <h3>Need Help Getting Started?</h3>
    <p>Download the <strong>MyMeetings app</strong> for the best experience finding and tracking AA meetings in {city}. Save your favorite meetings, track your attendance, get reminders, and access meeting information offline. MyMeetings indexes meetings across all 50 states and 300+ cities, making it the most comprehensive AA meeting finder available.</p>
  </div>
</section>
